cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DB. 

This paper is about using external knowledge sources, specifically knowledge graphs, to improve textual entailment. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing. The use of graph convolutional networks to encode the knowledge graphs suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper's focus on improving prediction accuracy suggests that it may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of knowledge graphs suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.DB (Databases).
